Bring a #medium pot{} of @salted water{} to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Finely chop @chili pepper{1}. Quarter @lime{1}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large pot{} over high heat. Add
@diced skinless dark meat chicken{10%ounce} and @salt{1/2%tsp} (1 tsp for 4 servings).
Using a #spatula{}, press into an even layer; cook, undisturbed, until lightly
browned on bottom, ~{2%minutes}.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

Break up chicken into pieces; add @bok choy and napa cabbage{4%ounce},
@garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, and half the chili (whole chili for 4).
(TIP: Use less chili if you prefer a milder soup!) Cook until chicken is
cooked through and veggies are slightly softened, ~{2-3%minutes} more.

> Swap in chicken or turkey for pork - no need to break up chicken into pieces.

Stir @pork ramen stock concentrate{1}, @chicken stock concentrate{1},
@veggie pho stock concentrate{1}, @curry powder{1%tablespoon},
@coconut milk{1%unit}, @sugar{1%tsp} (2 tsp for 4), and @water{1 1/2%cups} (3 cups
for 4 servings) into pot with chicken and veggies. Cover, bring to a boil, and
cook until veggies are tender, ~{2-4%minutes}.

While soup simmers, add @ramen noodles{4.5%ounce} to medium pot with boiling
water; cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Drain, then rinse noodles under cold water, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir drained noodles and a big squeeze of lime juice into pot with soup;
season with @salt{} and @pepper{} to taste.

Divide soup between #bowls{}. Squeeze juice from remaining lime wedges over
top and serve.